-2.2 Message Parsing -> When receives a sequence of octets that does not match HTTP-message grammar the server SHOULD respond with a 400 (Bad request)
-3. Request Line -> A server that receives a method longer thant any that it implements SHOULD respond with a 501.
-3. Request Line -> A server that receives a request-target onger than any URI it wishes to parse MUST respond with a 414
-5.1 Field Line Parsing -> Parse content of every field line
-5.1 Field Line Parsing -> A server must reject with a response status code of 400 message that contains whitespace ...
-5.2 Handle obsolete line folding
-6.1 Transfer Encoding -> A server that receives a request message with a transfer coding it does not understand should respond with 501
-6.1 -> A server MAY reject a request that contains both Content-Length and Transfer-Ecoding / The server MUST close the connection after responding ...
-6.1 -> A server or client that receives an HTTP/1.0 message containing a Transfer-Ecoding field MUST treat the message
-6.3 -> 5. If a message is received with an invalid Content-Length then the message must treat as an unrecoverable error and respond with a 400 ...
-6.3 -> 6. If the sender closes the connection the server must consider the message to be incomplete and close the connection

